&lt;/article&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><author>rabbitmq</author><guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.com/rabbitmq/rabbitmq-management</guid><pubDate>Mon, 03 Feb 2020 00:02:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>kivra/oauth2 #3 in Erlang, This week</title><link>https://github.com/kivra/oauth2</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Erlang Oauth2 implementation&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id="readme" class="md" data-path="README.md"&gt;&lt;article class="markdown-body entry-content p-5" itemprop="text"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a id="user-content-oauth2-v070--" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#oauth2-v070--"&gt;&lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;OAuth2 (v0.7.0)  &lt;a href="https://travis-ci.org/kivra/oauth2" rel="nofollow"&gt;&lt;img src="https://camo.githubusercontent.com/8157b15f31c1b2e5ef5aa0e16b5306f56022e7c3/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f6b697672612f6f61757468322e706e673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572" alt="BuildStatus" data-canonical-src="https://travis-ci.org/kivra/oauth2.png?branch=master" style="max-width:100%;"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This library is designed to simplify the implementation of the server side
of OAuth2 (&lt;a href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749" rel="nofollow"&gt;http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749&lt;/a&gt;). It provides
&lt;strong&gt;no&lt;/strong&gt; support for developing clients. See
&lt;a href="https://github.com/kivra/oauth2_client"&gt;oauth2_client&lt;/a&gt; for support in
accessing Oauth2 enabled services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;oauth2 is released under the terms of the &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License" rel="nofollow"&gt;MIT&lt;/a&gt; license&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current stable version: &lt;a href="https://github.com/kivra/oauth2/tree/0.6.1"&gt;0.6.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current Î± alpha version: &lt;a href="https://github.com/kivra/oauth2"&gt;0.7.x&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
